LONDON: The UAE on Friday condemned an attack that took place in the Israeli capital, Tel Aviv, a day earlier that killed and wounded a number of people and wished the injured a speedy recovery.
“The UAE Embassy in Tel Aviv strongly condemns the terrorist attack which took place in Dizingoff center and expresses its condolences to the families of the victims of this dreadful act,” it said in a tweet.  The #UAE Embassy in #TelAviv strongly condems the terrorist attack which took place in #Dizingoff center and expresses its condolences to the families of the victims of this dreadful act- may their memory be blessed- and we wish a speedy recovery to all those injured. — UAE Embassy in Israel (@UAEinIsrael) April 8, 2022 Earlier on Friday, Bahrain also condemned the attack, describing it as a “terrorist operation” and offering condolences to the families of the victims and the Israeli government.
“We reiterate the Kingdom of Bahrain’s position that opposes all forms of terrorism and violence no matter the motives and the justifications,” the foreign ministry said in a statement.
Both countries formally established relations with Israel in 2020 as part of the US-brokered Abraham Accords that also included Morocco.
A Palestinian who killed two people in a Tel Aviv bar late on Thursday was shot dead by Israeli security forces on Friday after an hours-long manhunt through the city.(With Reuters)